org.hibernate.metamodel.model.creation.spi

Interface RuntimeModelDescriptorFactory

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Serializable, Service

    public interface RuntimeModelDescriptorFactory
extends Service
    Contract for creating persister instances including EntityTypeDescriptor, PersistentCollectionDescriptor and EmbeddedTypeDescriptor
    See Also:
    RuntimeModelDescriptorClassResolver

    • Method Detail

      • createEntityDescriptor

        <J> EntityTypeDescriptor<J> createEntityDescriptor(EntityMapping bootMapping,
                                                   IdentifiableTypeDescriptor superTypeDescriptor,
                                                   RuntimeModelCreationContext creationContext)
                                            throws HibernateException
        Create an entity persister instance.

        A descriptor will not be completely usable after return from this method. The returned reference is good for linking references together, etc. The persister will be fully initialized later via Navigable.finishInitialization(java.lang.Object, org.hibernate.metamodel.model.creation.spi.RuntimeModelCreationContext)

        Parameters:
        bootMapping - The mapping information describing the entity
        superTypeDescriptor -
        creationContext - Access to additional information needed to create an EntityPersister
        Returns:
        An appropriate entity persister instance.
        Throws:
        HibernateException - Indicates a problem building the persister.

      • createPersistentCollectionDescriptor

        <O,C,E> PersistentCollectionDescriptor<O,C,E> createPersistentCollectionDescriptor(Property pluralProperty,
                                                                                   ManagedTypeDescriptor<O> runtimeManagedType,
                                                                                   RuntimeModelCreationContext creationContext)
                                                                            throws HibernateException
        Create a collection persister instance.

        A descriptor will not be completely usable after return from this method. The returned reference is good for linking references together, etc. The persister will be fully initialized later via PersistentCollectionDescriptor.finishInitialization(org.hibernate.mapping.Collection, org.hibernate.metamodel.model.creation.spi.RuntimeModelCreationContext)

        Throws:
        HibernateException - Indicates a problem building the persister.

      • finishUp

        default void finishUp(RuntimeModelCreationContext creationContext)
        Called after all entity mapping descriptors have been processed.
        Parameters:
        creationContext - Access to additional information
        "API Note:"
        Intended for custom implementors needing to perform some logic after all runtime descriptors are built
